{"nodes": [{"id": "draft6_0_idea_main_ideas_v1", "label": "main.ideas.v1 (decision record)", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "draft6.0\\idea\\main.ideas.v1.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "The running decision record: N1-N3 approved calls + supporting structure S1-S15, each phase's close-out delta; the committed plan."}, {"id": "draft6_0_idea_main_ideas_v1_boostresnet", "label": "BoostResNet (Huang, Ash, Langford, Schapire 2018)", "file_type": "paper", "source_file": "draft6.0\\idea\\main.ideas.v1.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "A ResNet is a telescoping sum of weak learners, each only slightly better than its predecessor; training error decays exponentially with depth. The theory behind N3 residual boosting blocks (guarantee lives on the labels -> GD checkpoints)."}, {"id": "draft6_0_idea_main_ideas_v1_byol_ema_view", "label": "BYOL EMA-view (momentum encoder)", "file_type": "paper", "source_file": "draft6.0\\idea\\main.ideas.v1.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "The de-risked upgrade to the plasticity gradient: read-layers learn fast but GD reads a slow EMA copy; the architecture already satisfies BYOL's anti-collapse conditions (asymmetry + stop-gradient). EMA-view worsened BWT in P9 (train/eval frame mismatch)."}, {"id": "draft6_0_idea_main_ideas_v1_llrd", "label": "LLRD (layer-wise learning-rate decay)", "file_type": "paper", "source_file": "draft6.0\\idea\\main.ideas.v1.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "The mirror of the plasticity gradient: same principle (slow what the downstream learner reads), flipped depth axis (LLRD slows the bottom; here the namer reads the top, so slow the top)."}, {"id": "draft6_0_idea_main_ideas_v1_distance_forward", "label": "Distance-Forward (margin loss + DF-O overlap)", "file_type": "paper", "source_file": "draft6.0\\idea\\main.ideas.v1.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Provides the margin loss kept on standby if SCFF log-loss is mushy, and DF-O overlapping blocks (group two adjacent layers, let gradient cross the pair) as the coordination half of N2."}, {"id": "draft6_0_idea_main_ideas_v1_ranpac", "label": "RanPAC (closed-form namer)", "file_type": "paper", "source_file": "draft6.0\\idea\\main.ideas.v1.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Frozen random ReLU projection -> running-Gram ridge prototype (W=(G+lambda I)^-1 M) + a class-balanced-reservoir guard. The committed namer at Phase 7 (S11): no gradient, closed-form, streaming. The 20% is NOT gradient descent. ~200x SLDA's cost -> SLDA deployed in P8."}, {"id": "draft6_0_idea_main_ideas_v1_slda", "label": "SLDA (deployed streaming namer)", "file_type": "paper", "source_file": "draft6.0\\idea\\main.ideas.v1.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Streaming LDA: the cheaper (metered ~69x cheaper than RanPAC) no-gradient namer deployed in P8; ties accuracy live; more robust on depth-less inputs. Resolves S11's cost caveat."}, {"id": "draft6_0_idea_main_ideas_v1_ddm_gate", "label": "DDM awake gate (on error-EMA)", "file_type": "paper", "source_file": "draft6.0\\idea\\main.ideas.v1.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "The committed economy gate: a two-threshold Drift Detection Method on the namer's error-EMA; meters the 80/20 real (GD-share 0.121). The class-direction tap-drift trigger was validated but NOT shipped (DDM consumes an error rate). The gate is a SAFETY mechanism."}, {"id": "draft6_0_idea_main_ideas_v1_cbrs", "label": "CBRS (class-balanced reservoir eviction)", "file_type": "paper", "source_file": "draft6.0\\idea\\main.ideas.v1.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "The committed bounded-LUT eviction policy (P9.3): best-bounded, ties the herding magnitude null, beats reservoir/recency; the holding cap grows with #classes (a memory-scaling law). Also the P7 imbalance guard (cbrs, not AIR)."}, {"id": "draft6_0_idea_main_ideas_v1_infonce_contrast_objective", "label": "InfoNCE contrast objective (supersedes energy-goodness)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "draft6.0\\idea\\main.ideas.v1.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "P3 adopted: a discriminative contrast (InfoNCE two-mask) objective preserves CLASS (composes depth) where the energy objective Sigma h^2 preserves only DENSITY (rots from layer 1). Supersedes energy-goodness. Sharper temp 0.2 (P5/T3) earns the depth back for free."}, {"id": "draft6_0_idea_main_ideas_v1_coordination_window", "label": "Coordination window (cross-layer w>=2)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "draft6.0\\idea\\main.ideas.v1.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "A forward-only cross-layer window (w>=2) that lets neighbours share context so depth composes; credit-chain LENGTH composes depth (not path multiplicity - overlap struck in T3). w4 = bounded depth-closer; dominated on cost by temperature."}, {"id": "draft6_0_idea_main_ideas_v1_noise_aug_contrast", "label": "NoiseAugContrast (noise-hardened SCFF, S10)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "draft6.0\\idea\\main.ideas.v1.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "P6 fix: corrupt one InfoNCE view with broad iid noise (sigma_aug=1.0) at train time; hardens the tap channel forward-only, improves clean acc, passes the A6 continual gate. Corrections: the fix is GENERIC not directional-specific; the enemy is a coherent translation along the class axis (retention is the direction-read)."}, {"id": "draft6_0_idea_main_ideas_v1_decision_record", "label": "The decision record (N1-N3 + S1-S15)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "draft6.0\\idea\\main.ideas.v1.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "The committed ledger: N1 SCFF stays cheap brain, N2 middle=stability+coordination (later struck), N3 GD=residual boosting (later superseded); S1-S15 supporting structure and each phase's close-out delta up to the S14 fair-race verdict and S15 limit map."}], "edges": [{"source": "draft6_0_idea_main_ideas_v1", "target": "draft6_0_idea_ideas1", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "draft6.0\\idea\\main.ideas.v1.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "draft6_0_idea_main_ideas_v1", "target": "draft6_0_idea_main_ideas_v1_decision_record", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "draft6.0\\idea\\main.ideas.v1.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "draft6_0_idea_main_ideas_v1", "target": "draft6_0_idea_main_ideas_v1_boostresnet", "relation": "cites", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "draft6.0\\idea\\main.ideas.v1.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "draft6_0_idea_main_ideas_v1", "target": "draft6_0_idea_main_ideas_v1_byol_ema_view", "relation": "cites", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "draft6.0\\idea\\main.ideas.v1.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "draft6_0_idea_main_ideas_v1", "target": "draft6_0_idea_main_ideas_v1_llrd", "relation": "cites", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "draft6.0\\idea\\main.ideas.v1.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "draft6_0_idea_main_ideas_v1", "target": "draft6_0_idea_main_ideas_v1_distance_forward", "relation": "cites", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "draft6.0\\idea\\main.ideas.v1.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "draft6_0_idea_main_ideas_v1", "target": "draft6_0_idea_main_ideas_v1_ranpac", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "draft6.0\\idea\\main.ideas.v1.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "draft6_0_idea_main_ideas_v1", "target": "draft6_0_idea_main_ideas_v1_slda", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "draft6.0\\idea\\main.ideas.v1.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "draft6_0_idea_main_ideas_v1", "target": "draft6_0_idea_main_ideas_v1_ddm_gate", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "draft6.0\\idea\\main.ideas.v1.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "draft6_0_idea_main_ideas_v1", "target": "draft6_0_idea_main_ideas_v1_cbrs", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "draft6.0\\idea\\main.ideas.v1.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "draft6_0_idea_main_ideas_v1", "target": "draft6_0_idea_main_ideas_v1_infonce_contrast_objective", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "draft6.0\\idea\\main.ideas.v1.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "draft6_0_idea_main_ideas_v1", "target": "draft6_0_idea_main_ideas_v1_coordination_window", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "draft6.0\\idea\\main.ideas.v1.md", "source_location"